name: The Murder Tapes
overview: Incorporating bodycam footage from the initial crime scene, surveillance video, and interrogation room recordings, homicide investigations unfold through dramatic real video footage  providing an up-close perspective on homicide investigations.

episodes.name: Albuquerque Ambush
episodes.overview: Don Fluitt is dead. Now, body-cam video and original audio capture the detectives hunt for his killer. As the case unravels, security video captures the moments just before the evil deed and a surprising twist will bring this killer to their knees.

episodes.name: Scene of the Crime
episodes.overview: When Brad McGarry is discovered murdered in his basement, residents in this sleepy coal mining town are left in shock. Detectives suspect robbery but then a friend comes forward and points them in the direction of someone whom they least expected.

episodes.name: Jane Doe
episodes.overview: Judith Therianos is a free-spirit; someone who very much wants to see the good in everyone. But Florida detectives unearth video surveillance that shows her utterly alone and blissfully unaware of the danger just moments before her life is cut short.

episodes.name: Frenzy
episodes.overview: Billy Shuler is dead. Now, video and audio capture the detectives desperate hunt for his killer. As the case slowly unravels, someone comes forward and identifies Billy's murderer. When the US Marshals get involved, the killer is brought to justice.

episodes.name: Don't Go In There
episodes.overview: Beverly Puccio is brutally murdered and found at home by an oddly behaving ex-boyfriend. Detectives use security and traffic cam footage to piece together the last night of her life including an encounter with a stranger to find her killer.

episodes.name: I Did It
episodes.overview: Michelle Kinney is found murdered in her apartment in Dubuque, Iowa. Her neighbors are puzzled. Local detectives unveil a haunting truth, leading to a shocking confession from an unlikely murderer.

episodes.name: Lost in the Desert
episodes.overview: Steven Begay is a loving uncle whose nephews see as a protector. So, the irony could not be greater when his bloody body is found near a playground in New Mexico. A manhunt ensues leaving police with a major discovery that turns the case on its head.

episodes.name: Puzzle Piece
episodes.overview: When the battered body of Bianca Rainer, mother of two young girls, is found in rural Arkansas, the police have just one unusual clue, a puzzle piece found stuck to her body. But they know if they find the missing puzzle, they will find her murderer.

episodes.name: The Bloody Footprint
episodes.overview: Maurice Goins, a friendly neighbor who provides meals to other tenants in his apartment complex, is found murdered in his bedroom. The case goes cold, until Lakewood, Ohio police suddenly receive a tip and the investigation is thrown into overdrive.

episodes.name: Fire in the Desert
episodes.overview: Albuquerque, N.M., mail carrier Marilyn Gandert disappears for days and no one knows where she has gone; when her body is found in the desert, detectives must find the murderer, and they only have a few witnesses beyond Marilyn's family members.

episodes.name: Is That Blood?
episodes.overview: True crime investigation using body-camera footage from police departments all over America.

episodes.name: Dying Words
episodes.overview: Steven Galvin is dead; now, bodycam video captures the detectives' hunt for his killer; as the case unravels, a surprise witness turns the case on its head; and a play by play of the crime reveals new evidence that brings the killer to justice.

episodes.name: Tape The Scene
episodes.overview: Agnes Bram, an 82-year-old Middleton, Wis., woman is found murdered in her garage; as detectives develop their case, a city-wide manhunt follows, and investigators must curb public hysteria by ensuring the killer will not kill again.

episodes.name: Down by Fire
episodes.overview: Ryne Zahner is an inspiration to his high school math students in Arizona. His friends see him as one of the nicest people they know. When a hooded murderer guns him down after a night of partying, the entire community struggles to grasp his murder.

episodes.name: Stay With Us, Madison
episodes.overview: Madison Wells, a sixteen-year-old student in New Jersey, is found murdered in her aunt's kitchen. When police look into her relationship with a twenty-year-old, they go down a rabbit hole that exposes an abusive relationship with a tragic end.

episodes.name: Who Shot Buckii?
episodes.overview: It's the middle of the night when Delvin "Buckii" Meadows is shot and killed in his neighbor's yard. As police investigate, it's not until witnesses come forward with information that detectives realize they may be the key to finding Delvin's killer.

episodes.name: The Truth is Dangerous
episodes.overview: Ty Underwood, a transgender woman, is found shot to death in her car, leaving detectives to wonder if she may have been a victim of a hate crime. Detectives use text messages, social media posts, and surveillance footage to track down her killer.

episodes.name: Things Weigh on You
episodes.overview: Jeffrey Franklin, a deaf 16-year-old, is dead. Now, body-cam video and original audio capture the hunt for what happened. As the investigation unravels, GPS data and shocking admissions give Jeffrey the justice he desperately deserves.

episodes.name: Don't Look Back
episodes.overview: Karen Simek is a talented food service worker. When her body is found with a gunshot wound outside her office in the early morning hours, it leaves her family in shock and sparks a year-long investigation, which ultimately leads detectives to her killer.

episodes.name: The Back of the Shed
episodes.overview: A backyard shed in a Michigan trailer park holds the answers to a dark secret regarding a missing teenage couple. Police interview their families, but one member is evasive, deepening the mystery and setting off a covert manhunt across the Midwest.

episodes.name: He's Not Going to Stop
episodes.overview: A spree shooter is on the loose in Scottsdale, and the entire city holds its breath while waiting for the culprit to be identified. Bodycam footage captures the tension as police try to nab a killer who always seems to be one step ahead.

episodes.name: The Last Laugh
episodes.overview: What appears to be a missing person's case, takes a stunning turn when very different portraits of her are revealed. Now, detectives must weed through a series of tangled relationships to uncover where Dawn has been all along.

episodes.name: This Guy's Getting Paranoid
episodes.overview: Roaa Al-Dhanoon has disappeared. What begins as a missing persons case, takes a turn by someone who is closest to her. Now, detectives must unravel a complex web of deceit that continues to strike fear throughout the devastated community.

episodes.name: The Girl in the Crowd
episodes.overview: What starts out as a calm night at the American Legion in Evansville, Indiana, quickly takes a turn when Anthony Blaylock is shot dead. But when detectives obtain video surveillance showing who is responsible, they stop at nothing to find his killer.

episodes.name: The Girl in the Park
episodes.overview: A deceased female's brutally beaten and sexually assaulted body turns up in Farmington, New Mexico. With an unidentified victim and plenty of suspects, detectives struggle with one of the most challenging "whodunits" of their career.

episodes.name: I'd Kill Them Again
episodes.overview: A man returns home from work, unaware of the grisly horrors awaiting him.

episodes.name: Footprints in the Snow
episodes.overview: The community in Bozeman, Montana, is rocked when officers find Lauren DeWise deceased and her roommate, Ashley Van Hemert, critically injured. As police search for clues, they realize that they must dive deep into Lauren's life to find her killer.

episodes.name: What's in the Backpack?
episodes.overview: Robert Sharp is a retired professor living in Ann Arbor, Michigan, and the last person anyone would expect to be murdered. But when he turns up brutally stabbed and burned, Robert's final moments make police wonder who could have done this and why.

episodes.name: Cover the Camera and I'll Talk
episodes.overview: The Sheriff's Office in Virginia's Isle of Wight County discovers a double homicide involving an 80-year-old disabled grandmother. An undercover informant, a hidden handgun, and an unusual confession all lead to convictions in this cold-blooded crime.

episodes.name: The Move Out
episodes.overview: Bodycam and CCTV capture the hunt for the killer who murdered three people. Twisted tales lead detectives on a wild goose chase, but the killers are revealed and must face the consequences.

episodes.name: She Set Me Up
episodes.overview: Indiana police rely on an unlikely source of information as they search for the person responsible for the shooting of 28-year-old D'Angelo White.

episodes.name: The Robin Tattoo
episodes.overview: A dismembered torso turns up in a Florida forest, and the discovery launches detectives across the US to search for answers. With only a tattoo found on the victim, investigators must solve this horrific mystery before the killer is gone for good.

episodes.name: Kind of a Vicious Person
episodes.overview: Apache County Sheriff's Office begins a double homicide investigation after the gruesome discovery of an elderly couple's remains in Sanders, Arizona. A statewide hunt for the perpetrator challenges veteran investigators resulting in an unusual arrest.

episodes.name: The Drop Off
episodes.overview: Ahmad Shad Laster’s loved ones are grief-stricken when he is shot outside a friend’s home; Flagler County, Fla., detectives uncover evidence that blows the case wide open, but the hunt for justice tests family bonds and reveals shocking secrets

episodes.name: Blunt Force Trauma
episodes.overview: A woman of faith, Susan Hernandez, is the last person police would expect to find murdered in her basement; searching for suspects, detectives turn over every stone in the hunt for Susan’s killer, with a result that shakes the town to its core.

episodes.name: Fled on Foot
episodes.overview: Police race to catch a killer, but first, they must keep the witness alive.

episodes.name: The House on Lillian Street
episodes.overview: Samantha Guthrie's parents desperately search for their missing child. As the police search reveals many players in this mystery, there is one common thread - the Lillian St. house. Police aim to find the truth of what occurred within those walls.

episodes.name: A Really Odd Situation
episodes.overview: In Grand Rapids, Mich., local mother Laurie Lundeberg lies dead from gunshots outside her home; detectives must track down the culprit and uncover their motive for shooting Laurie; making matters worse, the killer strikes again.

episodes.name: Something Came Over Me
episodes.overview: In Akron, Ohio, local antiques dealer Mary Kay Wohlfarth mysteriously vanishes into thin air; detectives race to find the elderly woman, leaving no stone unturned; however, finding Mary Kay might lead to more questions than answers.

episodes.name: Smokescreen
episodes.overview: Detectives in Waynesfield, Ohio, contend with a grim mystery when they discover the lifeless body of Erin Mulcahy in her shower. The pressure is now on the police department to catch those responsible for the town's first murder in over fifty years.

episodes.name: The Man in the Red Shirt
episodes.overview: Forty-year-old Jamie Baker leaves behind her family when someone shoots and kills her with a bullet through the back. The mystery only deepens when police dig into her last moments and uncover what transpired the night of her death.

episodes.name: Body in the Yard
episodes.overview: When workers find a body on an abandoned property in western Ohio, it opens up a homicide investigation that sends shockwaves through the Amish community.

episodes.name: The Quick Change
episodes.overview: The town of Fort Smith, Arkansas, reels when an elderly, retired school teacher turns up dead, bludgeoned to death with a hammer no fewer than 36 times. When the person responsible receives justice, an unlikely perpetrator comes to light.

episodes.name: Blue Nightmare
episodes.overview: Local police confront their worst fears when the body of a local EMT is found at her home in Columbus, Georgia. The ensuing investigation shocks the wider community and tests the public's faith in law enforcement itself.

episodes.name: The Smoke Shop in the Truck
episodes.overview: Flagler County Sheriff's Office investigates the shooting of an 18-year-old high school track star, Curtis Israel Gray. The case threatens to go cold before a source close to home delivers the prime suspect straight to Sheriff's front door.

episodes.name: Two Neighbors
episodes.overview: A chilling confession ultimately tells all after a relative finds Cindy Testerman strangled to death in her own home and a second woman goes missing.

episodes.name: Sergeant Hassel
episodes.overview: Officers find Tyrone Hassel III shot to death outside his father's home while on holiday leave from the Army; investigators must unravel a real whodunit, and when the killer finally reveals themselves, the detectives can't hide their shock.

episodes.name: Follow the Tracks
episodes.overview: The Bryan, Texas, Police Department investigates the shooting of 23-year-old local landscaper, Jose Armando Pina; a masked perpetrator flees the area via a path thick with brambles, leaving behind vital evidence.

episodes.name: I Did Something Real Bad
episodes.overview: A body is left on a Milwaukee street, creating intrigue and mystery.

episodes.name: Club Chaos
episodes.overview: Lima, Ohio, police race to a chaotic scene at an after-hours nightclub following a shooting that leaves one person dead and multiple others injured. As they try to identify the shooter, dozens of patrons flee in fear, confusing first responders.

episodes.name: Blood in the Snow
episodes.overview: Noah Kinney is shot dead in a car that crashed outside a home in Akron, Ohio, and detectives race to find an armed killer on the loose, but ultimately investigators are shocked to discover the video evidence that solve the case.

episodes.name: The Elder Murders
episodes.overview: A 911 call comes in from a woman who says her neighbor is not breathing and covered in blood, then police find 69-year-old Benjamin dead, his house in disarray and money missing, but as detectives search for answers, another murder occurs.

episodes.name: Killer on Camera
episodes.overview: Akron police officers respond to a shooting outside a bar on a busy Friday night on Main Street; what starts out as a shooting investigation turns into a mystery of murder and the hunt for a cold-blooded killer.

episodes.name: Who Killed the Landlord?
episodes.overview: After a man calls 911 to report being stabbed and a house on fire, police find Ron Whiles shot and burned in his home in Lafayette, Ind.; with one victim dead and one clinging to life, detectives question multiple suspects, which leads to one name.

episodes.name: Murder of Convenience
episodes.overview: Akron officers respond to a shooting outside a convenience store; they find Dereke Alexander bleeding with a faint pulse, but he doesn't survive; the investigation leads detectives to two cold-blooded killers who stalked and hunted the man.

episodes.name: For Love or Money
episodes.overview: In separate calls, Chillicothe, Ohio, police officers find three murder victims and another clinging to life. As they investigate these crimes, they discover the victims are related. Detectives question suspects, which leads to an unlikely killer.

episodes.name: Three Days, Six Murders
episodes.overview: Newnan, Georgia, Police respond to six murders in three days. As investigators try to piece together the motive behind the killings, several witnesses claim to know who is responsible -- but a rush to judgment could result in a killer going free.

episodes.name: A Shot in the Dark
episodes.overview: Ida Mae Ford gets shot dead in the middle of a dark street near her home in Macon, Georgia; detectives race to track down the beloved grandmother's elusive killer, and a shocking crime spree ultimately leads investigators to an unexpected suspect.
